#Hadean eon
lower output of Sun
formation of Moon
asteroids and comets bring water
heavy CO2/N2 atmosphere, high pressure, greenhouse effects
liquid water oceans with temperature 200C+

#Archean eon (4-2.5 Gy)
first cells (archaea, bacteria)
tectonic plates

#Proterozoic eon (2.5-0.5 Gy)
Great Oxidation Event: cyanobacteria, rise of oxygen
Huronian glaciation: ice ages
first multicellular organisms: fungi, plants, animals (sponges)
Columbia supercontinent
Rodinia supercontinent
Cryogenian ice ages: Sturtian and Marinoan glaciation, evolution of algae
Ediacaran biota: tubular sessile organisms
Avalon explosion: diversification of animals (bilateral)

#Cambrian
Pannotia supercontinent
Cambrian explosion: diversification of animals
- Arthropoda: Trilobita, Megacheira, Radiodonta, Crustacea
Archaeocyatha: sessile sponges, appear and become extinct
Agronomic revolution: animal burrowing sea floor

#Ordovician
Great Ordovician Biodiversification Event
- Cephalopoda: Nautiloidea, Orthoceratoidea
- Gastropoda
- corals
- jawless fish
- Eurypterida (sea scorpions)

#Silurian
Caledonian orogeny: Laurentia + Baltica collision
- Svalbard
- Scandinavian Mountains
- Scottish Highlands
terrestrial arthropods: Myriapoda, Hexapoda, Arachnida
jawed fish, armored jawless fish

#Devonian
plants: ferns

#Carboniferous
Alleghanian orogeny: North America + Africa collision
- Appalachian Mountains
- Atlas Mountains
winged insects
amphibians
plants: Lepidodendrales (scale trees)

#Permian
reptiles

#Triassic
Archosaurs
first mammals
Uralian orogeny: Baltica + Siberia collision
- Ural Mountains

#Triassic-Jurassic extinction event

#Jurassic
humid climate, high CO2 levels
Dinosaurs
conifers, cycads, ferns
first birds, snakes, turtles, crabs
breakup of Pangea to Laurasia and Gondwana

#Cretaceous
flowering plants
climate cools
Andean orogeny
Gondwana split into South America-Africa + India + Australia–Antarctica
South America-Africa split

#Paleogene
mammals diversification
Iceland
Australia–Antarctica split
Persia–Tibet–Burma orogeny
Alpine orogeny
- Apennine Mountains
- Alps
- Dinaric alps
- Carpathian Mountains
- Taurus Mountains
- Caucasus Mountains
- Zagros Mountains

#Oligocene
Paratethys: shallow sea, new remnant Black Sea + Caspian Sea + Aral Sea
opening of Tasmanian Passage and Drake Passage

#Neogene

#Quaternary: glacial periods, megafauna
Heinrich event: large break off from ice sheet
Last Glacial Maximum (25-20kY)
- Sahul: Australia + Tasmania + Papua New Guinea
- Sundaland: SE Asia + Borneo + Sumatra + Java + Bali
- Beringia: Asia-North-America land bridge
- Doggerland: land between Great Britain + Netherlands + Denmark, now shallow North Sea
- Gulf of Thailand + Persian Gulf above sea level
Younger Drayds (12kY): temporary return to glacial conditions

#Pleistocene
Lake Agassiz: proglacial, now remnant Winnipeg and Manitoba lakes
Lake Corcoran: California valley, now remnant Tulare Lake
Lake Lahontan: NW Nevada
Lake Bonneville: Utah, now remnant Great Salt Lake
Lake Cahuilla: south California, now Salton Sea

#Holocene
African humid period (AHP): savanna and lakes in Sahara
